&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="k">1.&lt;/span> List every &lt;span class="sb">`yaml.load`&lt;/span>, &lt;span class="sb">`yaml.full_load`&lt;/span>,
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> &lt;span class="sb">`yaml.load(..., Loader=yaml.Loader)`&lt;/span>,
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> &lt;span class="sb">`yaml.load(..., Loader=yaml.UnsafeLoader)`&lt;/span>,
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> &lt;span class="sb">`yaml.load(..., Loader=yaml.FullLoader)`&lt;/span> call.
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="k">2.&lt;/span> Read the lockfile and confirm the pinned PyYAML version.
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="gu">## Step 1 — Apply the generic fix pattern
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="gu">&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">Follow the recipe at
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">[/prompt-library/general/classic-vulnerable-defaults/pyyaml-load/]
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">end-to-end. Replace every unsafe call with &lt;span class="sb">`yaml.safe_load`&lt;/span>,
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">or install the import-time shim, or both.
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="gu">## Step 2 — Pin PyYAML
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="gu">&lt;/span>
