&lt;h2>Verification — what the reviewer looks for&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="verification--what-the-reviewer-looks-for">&lt;/span>
&lt;a href="#verification--what-the-reviewer-looks-for" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section">&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Every call site touched, or shim installed, with a clear
rationale per call.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>PyYAML pinned to ≥6.0.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>SCA output shows CVE-2017-18342 cleared.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Behaviour-preservation test for any custom YAML tag the
codebase uses.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2>Watch for&lt;span class="hx:absolute hx:-mt-20" id="watch-for">&lt;/span>
&lt;a href="#watch-for" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section">&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>&lt;code>yaml.load_all&lt;/code> and &lt;code>yaml.full_load_all&lt;/code>.&lt;/strong> Same problem,
same fix.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Indirect callers.&lt;/strong> Some libraries ship their own
&lt;code>yaml.load(...)&lt;/code> wrapper — fix the library or pin it past
the patched version.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>PyYAML 6.x parser changes.&lt;/strong> A handful of edge-case
documents parse differently in 6.x (octal-number rules,
some boolean shortcuts). Run the project&amp;rsquo;s tests.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
